3475. " {\"type\": \"proof\"," : String
3476. "  \"text\":" : String
3477. "  \"By Lemma 9, l factors through a homogeneous pseudo-length function barL : G_ab -> R. By Lemma 11, barL factors through the torsion-free quotient A:=G_ab/T(G_ab); let tildeL : A -> R be the induced homogeneous pseudo-length function. By Lemma 12, tildeL extends to a seminorm on VQ:=A tensor_Z Q. By Lemma 13, there exist a real Banach space B and a canonical map VQ -> B preserving the seminorm. Define phi:G -> B to be the composite G -> G_ab -> A -> VQ -> B. Each arrow is a group homomorphism when B is regarded additively, so phi is a group homomorphism. By construction l(g)=||phi(g)||_B for every g. If l is a length function and phi(g)=0, then l(g)=||phi(g)||_B=0; hence g=e. Thus phi is injective.\"," : String
